<h2 class="bold border-bottom mb4 pb2">Tables</h2>

<div class="mb4 pb2">

  <h3 class="bold mb1">Borderless Tables</h3>

  <p class="mb3">You can add tables without using any classes at all. Just use the table, th, tr and td html elements to build. When considering whether or not to use the table element, consider whether or not the information inside is tabular data. Additionally, you can set the width of individual columns using <a href="/layout/grid">our grid's column classes,</a> as show below:</p>

  <table class="mb3 xs-col-12 md-col-10">
    <tr>
      <th class="col-6">Title</th>
      <th class="col-3">Views</th>
      <th class="col-3">Social Lift</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>16 Easy Cheese Hacks That Will Blow Your Mind</td>
      <td>1,241</td>
      <td>1.1x</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>18 Times George Michael Bluth Understood You On A Personal Level</td>
      <td>6,468</td>
      <td>1.2x</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Here’s An Epic Video Of Arnold Schwarzenegger Blowing A Bunch Of Sh*t Up</td>
      <td>8,516</td>
      <td>1.7x</td>
    </tr>
  </table>

  <p>Here's what it looks like in code:</p>

<pre><code class="html"><%='<table>'%>
  <%='<tr>'%>
    <%='<th class="col-6">Title</th>'%>
