  <h3 class="bold mb1">Faux Table Layout</h3>

  <p class="mb3">Sometimes, you'll want to give content the layout properties of a table without using the html elements. Using the classnames <code class="js-highlight">.table</code>, <code class="js-highlight">.th</code>, <code class="js-highlight">.tr</code> and <code class="js-highlight">.td</code>, you can add a table layout to non-tabular content.</p>

  <div class="table mb3">
    <div class="td fill-gray-lighter border-right p2">Lines of different lengths</div>
    <div class="td fill-gray-lighter border-right p2">Will automatically expand their inner divs to be as tall as each other.</div>
    <div class="td fill-gray-lighter p2">Because tables are the most amazing things in the whole world don't you agree? Wait where are you going? Come back!</div>
  </div>

  <p>And the code:</p>

<pre><code class="html"><%='<div class="table">'%>
  <%='<div class="td">Lines of different lengths</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="td">Will automatically expand their inner divs to be as tall as each other.</div>'%>
  <%='<div class="td">Because tables are the most amazing things in the whole world don\'t you agree? Wait where are you going? Come back!</div>'%>
<%='</div>'%></code></pre>

